{{Quote|Fud Sang is down there. Well, I thought he was serving four life sentences here at Oovo IV.|Fode Annodue|audio=Fode-FudSang.flac|<ref name="Star Wars Episode I: Racer">[[Star Wars: Episode I Racer|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''Racer'']]</ref>}}
'''Desolation Alley''' was a [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] maximum security [[Prison/Legends|prison]] on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] [[Oovo IV/Legends|Oovo IV]]. Notable prisoners included [[Aurra Sing/Legends|Aurra Sing]], [[Fud Sang/Legends|Fud Sang]], and [[Bendix Fust]]. During the last [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of the Galactic Republic, [[Fenn Booda]] served as the prison [[Warden/Legends|warden]].

In addition to corrections officers and security guards, the prison was patrolled by [[RC-AD Riot Control/Assault Droid]]s. [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaughts]] were made [[Engineer/Legends|engineers]] in the prison, usually keeping up on maintenance and repairs, especially the crucial deflector shield generators.

[[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]], while escaping an unsuccessful [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]] mission, acquired (via thievery) his infamous prototype [[Firespray-31-class patrol and attack craft/Legends|''Firespray-31''-class patrol and attack craft]] [[Slave I/Legends|''Slave I'']] here.

By [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]], the prison became famous for [[Podracing/Legends|podracing]]. It was later destroyed by the forces of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]].

